(1, '2017-02-11 20:27:00', '2017-05-01 14:14:07', NULL, 'KPJ Sentosa Launches New Name', 'One of Kuala Lumpurs first private hospitals made a historic change today, changing its name from Sentosa Medical Centre to KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hosiptal (KPJ Sentosa).', NULL, NULL, '07/03/2016', 'http://www2.kpjsentosa.com.my/uploads/1-17-05-01-10-14-07.jpg', 'KPJ Sentosa Launches New Name', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div class="blog-content"><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><em>Kuala Lumpur, 7 March 2016 </em>&nbsp; One of Kuala Lumpurs first private hospitals made a<br>historic change today, changing its name from Sentosa Medical Centre to KPJ Sentosa<br>KL Specialist Hosiptal (KPJ Sentosa).</p><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify">Encik Mohd. Taufik Ismail, the hospitals Executive Director, said The hospital has been<br>serving patients for more than 40 years since it first opened its doors to the public in 1972.<br>This name change is a testimony of our continued efforts to enhance and strengthen<br>its presence in the city.<br><br><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0087.jpg" src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0087.jpg" style="height:362px; width:647px"></p><p><br></p><div class="mid-body"><div class="body-content"><div class="left-panel">KPJ Sentosa is a 122-bed hospital which houses an extensive range of medical and surgical<br>specialties led by clinical experts with more than 40 years experience in the respective<br>discipline. Among the niche services are Gastroenterology, Gynaecological Oncology,<br>Orthopaedic &amp; Trauma Surgery, and other minimally invasive surgeries. <p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify">In Urology, KPJ Sentosa has taken another step forward with its state-of-the-art<br>minimally invasive care for kidney stones such as n<strong>on-invasive extracorporeal shock<br>wave lithotripsy (ESWL)</strong><strong>,</strong> p<strong><span style="font-family:">ercutaneous nephrolithotomy </span></strong>and<strong> </strong><strong>Ureteroscopy</strong><strong>.</strong></p><br><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0089.jpg" src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0089.jpg" style="height:360px; width:642px"><br><br><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify">In 2006, Sentosa was acquired by KPJ Healthcare Berhad (KPJ), one Malaysias leading providers<br>of private healthcare services with 25 hospitals located nationwide. The acquisition<br>enabled Sentosa to leverage on KPJs integrated network of services and contribute<br>extensively to the hospitals broader range of services.&nbsp; </p><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify">The hospital new name was officially launched by KPJs President &amp; Managing Director,<br>YBhg Dato Amiruddin Abdul Satar.&nbsp; </p><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify">Also present during the event was Puan Hajjah Jasimah Hassan, Chairman of KPJ Sentosa,<br>Mohd Taufik Ismail, Executive Director of KPJ Sentosa, Dr&nbsp; Mohd Harris Lu, Medical Director of<br>KPJ Sentosa KL, Puan Miranda Harumal, Chief Executive Officer of KPJ Sentosa KL ,<br>senior management of KPJ Healthcare Berhad, Consultants and Staff of KPJ Sentosa KL.<br><br><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0093.jpg" src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0093.jpg" style="height:362px; width:646px"></p><div class="container"><div class="mid-body"><div class="body-content"><div class="left-panel"><br><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><strong>In conjunction with the launch, KPJ Sentosa is providing special promotional packages from<br>7 March until 31<sup>st</sup> May 2016 for its 4-person family wellness package, a mother and baby<br>care package, a urological screening package and a women wellness package.&nbsp; &nbsp;</strong></p><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify">In 2015, KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital received the international Integrated<br>Management System (IMS) Certification by Bureau Veritas, comprising of ISO 9001:2008<br>Quality System, ISO 14001:2004 Environmental Management System, and OHSAS 18001:2007<br>Occupational Safety &amp; Health Management System. At par with other major industry players,<br>KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital is also fully accredited by the Malaysian Society for Quality<br>in Health (MSQH), a national accreditation body for health care facilities and services, thus<br>reflecting the organizations commitment towards being a quality healthcare provider.<br>Additionally, KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital is certified as a Baby Friendly Hospital (BFH)<br>by Ministry of Health, Malaysia since 2014. </p><br><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0078.jpg" src="http://kpjsentosa.com/uploads/IMG-20160307-WA0078.jpg" style="height:365px; width:651px"></div></div></div></div><p style="margin-left:0cm; margin-right:0cm; text-align:justify"><br></p></div></div></div></div>', '1', NULL, '2016-03-07'),
(3, '2017-02-20 14:44:35', '2017-05-01 13:55:24', NULL, 'KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospitals Pink Saves Amazing Race 2016', 'Pink Saves Amazing Race 2016 raises breast cancer awareness', NULL, NULL, '23/10/2016', 'http://www2.kpjsentosa.com.my/uploads/3-17-05-01-09-55-24.jpg', 'KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospitals Pink Saves Amazing Race 2016', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div class="blog-content"><p>Kuala Lumpur, 23 October 2016 - Tasik Titiwangsa was all dressed in pink as KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital celebrated its PinkSaves Amazing Race 2016 on 23rd October 2016.&nbsp; The event was in conjunction with Breast Cancer Awareness month celebrated worldwide every October.<br><br>Tuan Haji Mohd Taufik Ismail, Executive Director of KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital, said This is the hospitals second PinkSaves signature event, following its launch on 31st October 2015. It is specially focused on celebrating and raising awareness about womens health through various preventive screenings and awareness campaigns.<br><br>"This year, we wanted to give even more back to the general public.&nbsp; PinkSaves Amazing 2016 gathered more than 600 participants including cancer survivors from Majlis Kanser Negara (MAKNA) and 40 ladies from BERNAMAs Benita Biggest Loser 2016 program.<br><br>Winners of male and female category won cash prizes for the 5km run around Tasik Titiwangsa. Educational and fun activities were also held with sumptuous food from participating food trucks as well as free healthy beverages.<br><br>Taufik added "We are indeed overwhelmed by the support shown towards a good cause.<br>The event also witnessed a cheque presentation&nbsp;to MAKNA which were partly contributed from the participation fees.<br><br>In conjunction with the Awareness month, KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital is providing various promotional packages until December 2016.&nbsp;&nbsp; For more information, please visit www.kpjsentosa.com&nbsp;&nbsp;<br><br>In 2015, KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital received the international Integrated Management System (IMS) Certification by Bureau Veritas, comprising of ISO 9001:2008 Quality System, ISO 14001:2004 Environmental Management System, and OHSAS 18001:2007 Occupational Safety &amp; Health Management System.<br><br>At par with other major industry players, KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital is also fully accredited by the Malaysian Society for Quality in Health (MSQH), a national accreditation body for health care facilities and services, thus reflecting the organizations commitment towards being a quality healthcare provider. Additionally, KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital is certified as a Baby Friendly Hospital (BFH) by Ministry of Health, Malaysia since 2014.</p><p><br></p></div>', '1', NULL, '2016-10-23'),
(4, '2017-02-20 15:22:05', '2017-06-14 04:46:50', NULL, 'World Diabetes Day 2015 Promotion Booth', 'In conjunction with World Diabetes Day, the first 100 registrants at out Promotion Booth (Main Lobby) on 14th November 2015 (Saturday) will get a FREE BP and Blood Glucose check!', NULL, NULL, '14/11/2015', 'http://www2.kpjsentosa.com.my/uploads/4-17-05-01-09-56-06.jpg', 'World Diabetes Day 2015 Promotion Booth', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div class="blog-content"><br><div class="testimonials3 text-center"><div class="owl-carousel text-carousel"><div class="item"><div class="testimonials3-content"><h3>special promotional packages</h3><p><em>In conjunction with World Diabetes Day, the first 100 registrants at out Promotion Booth (Main Lobby) on 14th November 2015 (Saturday) will get a FREE BP and Blood Glucose check!</em></p></div></div><!--{cke_protected}{C}%3C!%2D%2D%20end%20item%20%2D%2D%3E--></div></div></div>', '0', NULL, '2015-11-14'),
(5, '2017-02-22 15:17:53', '2017-05-01 14:18:10', NULL, 'Launching of Pinksaves on 31st October 2015', 'KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital launched its inaugural event called, PinkSaves. The program set the tone for a deeper and greater awareness among the public, especially women, on the need to take action against cancer besides promoting the importance', NULL, NULL, '31/10/2015', 'http://www2.kpjsentosa.com.my/uploads/5-17-05-01-10-18-10.jpg', 'Launching of Pinksaves on 31st October 2015', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<div class="blog-content"><p>KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital formerly known as Sentosa Medical Centre launched its inaugural event called, PinkSaves. The program set the tone for a deeper and greater awareness among the public, especially women, on the need to take action against cancer besides promoting the importance embracing healthier lifestyle.</p><p>The main highlight of this event was the launching of the KPJ Sentosa KLs PinkSaves Screening<br>icon by Puan Jasimah Hassan, Chairman of KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital and the formation of the human pink ribbon in collaboration with 200 students of KPJ Healthcare University College (KPJUC) and more than 150 KPJ Sentosa KLs staffs.</p><p>Accordding to En Mohd Taufik Ismail, Executive Director of KPJ Sentosa KL, PinkSaves is the brainchild of KPJ Sentosa KL and the program is especially designed with womens health in mind. The screening icon extends the magnitude of Touch, Look &amp; Check towards minimizing cancer and maximizing life.</p><p>Also present during the event were Dr Mohd Harris Lu, Medical Director and Puan Miranda Harumal, General Manager of KPJ Sentosa KL Specialist Hospital, Prof. Dato Dr Lokman Saim, President / CEO KPJUC and Puan Zaila Idrus, General Manager of KPJUC.</p><p>Various fun filled contests were held for the public throughout the month of October namely Adult Coloring Therapy and Guess the PinkHearts in the Jar, where cash prizes were up for grabs. During the event, various activities such as photo booth, promotional booths, Im the Avatar, face painting and balloon sculpting were also held.</p><p>To commemorate the launch, special Mammography Screening promotion of RM 100 for 2 persons (exclude Radiologist fees), until 31st December 2015. It is with much hope that with this campaign, more women will come forward to get themselves screened early.</p>For more information, please call our PR &amp; Marketing Services at 03  4043 7166<div class="testimonials3 text-center"><div class="owl-carousel text-carousel"><div class="item"><div class="testimonials3-content"><h3>En MOHD TAUFIK ISMAIL (ED) :</h3><p><em>"PinkSaves is the brainchild of KPJ Sentosa KL and the program is especially designed with womens health in mind. The screening icon extends the magnitude of Touch, Look &amp; Check towards minimizing cancer and maximizing life.</em></p></div></div><!--{cke_protected}{C}%3C!%2D%2D%20end%20item%20%2D%2D%3E--></div></div></div>', '1', NULL, '2015-10-31'),
