(231, '2017-12-21 03:26:01', '2017-12-21 03:26:01', 'Abuzar', 'infobtsdelhi@gmail.com', '00917290045901', 'General', 'Empanelment', 'Dear Manager,\r\n\r\nKindly find our company profile attached to this mail. \r\n\r\nThis is a Request for Empanelment. \r\n\r\nWe at Bombay Travel Service would  like to introduce ourselves as a leading Overseas Executive & Manpower Consulting firm providing quality recruitment and training solutions to organizations in India and the MENA region . \r\nWe are registered with the Ministry of Overseas Indian Affairs as an overseas recruiting agency having recruiting authorisation vide license number:B-609/MUM/PER/1000+/5/1849/85 for the overseas recruitment.\r\n\r\nThe company has its presence in Mumbai ,New Delhi  and an extension office in Riyadh\r\n\r\n.\r\nWe specialize in the recruitment of the following: \r\nDoctors, nurses, pharmacists, physiotherapists and other paramedical staff. \r\nAt Bombay Travel Service, we will endeavour to surpass the service levels you have previously received from within the industry each and every time.\r\n\r\nLooking forward to be associated with your estee', '1', NULL, NULL),
(232, '2017-12-21 13:39:00', '2017-12-21 13:39:00', 'Mrs Leena', 'lk_keshu@hotmail.com', '+60192489042', 'Complaint', 'Security guard disrespect patient''s family', 'My bro in law admitted in HDW on 20th Dec due to severe injuries. Families and relatives from outstation took a visit since his condition very bad. Aft visiting hours few relative''s came from far and asked on duty nurse permission to visit him few minutes. A malay lady security guard came and asked us to leave the place in rude tone of voice. She waited at the door and chased us out. The nurse on duty also not cooperative and asked us to leave. We have no intention to disturb other patients but at the sametime we also in a situation worried abt our relative who is critical condition. Hope the management look into this matter and looking forward for a good feedback. \r\n\r\nThanks & regards,\r\nLeena', '1', NULL, NULL),
(233, '2017-12-21 16:11:35', '2017-12-21 16:11:35', 'Fatima Isaacs ', 'shazaray58@gmail.com', '0027215104939', 'Appointment', 'Dialysis for international patient ', 'My husband requires 2 x sessions of dialysis when we are in Kuala lumpur. First session Tuesday 2 January and second session 4 January. Please can you accommodate him. We are desperate. We have been let down by KPJ Tawakkal who first agreed but now say they have machine problems and can only take international patients from middle January ', '1', NULL, NULL),
(234, '2017-12-22 07:35:11', '2017-12-22 07:35:11', 'NUR NADIA BINTI ZULKARNA''IN', 'nurnadiazulkarnain@gmail.com', '013-7045972', 'Inquiry', 'Application for the Position of Pharmacy Assistant', 'Nur Nadia binti Zulkarnain\r\nNo.29, Jalan Delise 6, \r\nTaman Bandar Senawang,\r\n70450 Seremban,\r\nNegeri Sembilan Darul Khusus\r\n\r\n22nd December 2017\r\n\r\nHuman Resources Manager\r\n36 Jalan Cemor, Kompleks Damai, \r\n50400 Kuala Lumpur, Malaysia.\r\n\r\nDear Sir,\r\n\r\nApplication for the Position of Pharmacy Assistant\r\n\r\nPlease find enclosed my CV for your consideration for the position of Pharmacy Assistant. For your information, I have finished my study on Bachelor Pharmaceutical Science with Health Sciences (HONS.) form KPJ Healthcare University College, Nilai Campus for past few days. I also have finished my study on Diploma in Pharmacy (2014) at the same campus and having experienced in clinical attachment at your hospital. Meanwhile waiting for my final semester result and my graduation day on December 2018, I would like to work for KPJ Seremban Specialist Hospital.\r\n\r\nI am interested in working for KPJ Sentosa Specialist Hospital because of its outstanding reputation among people from Negeri S', '1', NULL, NULL),
